properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 13 at 3:40AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
Winds are expected to increase over the Interstate 80 Summit and
adjacent foothills this afternoon, and eventually over the High
Plains east of Interstate 25 after 2 PM MST. Wind gusts up to 55
MPH will be possible from the Interstate 80 Summit eastward into
the city of Cheyenne, as well as the entire Interstate 25 corridor
from the Colorado State line to Casper. Those driving light, high
profile vehicles or towing trailers should exercise extreme
caution today, especially on north to south oriented roads. A High
Wind Warning is already in effect for the Bordeaux area, along
Interstate 25 between Chugwater and Wheatland. Winds will slowly
subside overnight, but remain gusty.

NWSheadline: STRONG WINDS POSSIBLE LATE THIS AFTERNOON AND EVENING OVER PORTIONS OF SOUTHEAST WYOMING
